<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="580" pageId="3" pageNumber="579" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1812,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1920,1947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">Description.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[440,578,1920,1947]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="579" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="8.5">8.5–9.5 mm</quantity>
. Head, pronotum, antennae reddish brown; elytra black; legs pale yellowish red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1812,2019]" box="[199,1094,1993,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="579">Head stout, broad, glabrous, smooth; neck almost smooth. Eyes less protruding.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Pronotum as long as wide, glabrous, not exceeding the width of head with eyes; laterally convex, moderately narrowed before the base, hind angles not pointed, not projecting laterally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="580">Elytra convex, with faint, wide striations, having equally raised intervals; disc smooth with slight punctuations over the intervals.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
